among Logicians, the firft <a class="xref" href="vol0.html#article-MODE">mode</a> of the firft <a class="xref" href="vol0.html#article-FIGURE">figure</a> of syllogifms. A syllogifm in barbara is one whereof all the proportions are univerfal and affirmative; the middle <a class="xref" href="vol0.html#article-TERM">term</a> being the fubject of the firft proposition, and <a class="xref" href="vol0.html#article-ATTRIBUTE">attribute</a> in the <a class="xref" href="vol0.html#article-SECOND">second</a>.

*Examp.* <a class="xref" href="vol3.html#article-BAR">Bar</a>. Every wicked <a class="xref" href="vol0.html#article-MAN">man</a> is miserable;
Ba. All tyrants are wicked men;
Ra. Therefore all tyrants are miserable.
